# prompt.txt — Your project goal
#
# Copy this file to prompt.txt and replace the content below with your own goal.
# This file is excluded from git (.gitignore) because it is project-specific.
# The entire contents are injected into every Claude iteration as the OVERALL GOAL.
#
# Tips:
# - Be specific about what needs to be built and why
# - Include any architectural constraints or patterns to follow
# - Reference existing code or projects Claude should follow as examples
# - Include acceptance criteria if known
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------

## Goal

Briefly describe what you want to build. Example:

Add a recurring background job that reads records from a CSV file, validates them,
and upserts into the database. The job should run on a configurable schedule,
archive processed files, and follow the same patterns as the existing ImportJob.

## Constraints

- List any files or areas that must not be modified
- List naming conventions or coding standards to follow
- List any third-party libraries already in use that should be reused

## Reference

- Point to any existing code that should be used as a pattern
- e.g. C:\Repos\MyProject\src\Jobs\ExistingJob.cs
